definition: ten (used in fractions, writing checks etc)/assorted/miscellaneous
suffix, used to form interrogative 什麼|什么[shen2 me5], what?, indefinite 這麼|这么[zhe4 me5] thus, etc
what are you doing?/what's he up to?

pinyin: shen2 me5 feng1 ba3 ni3 chui1 lai2 de5

definition: it takes all sorts (to make a world) (idiom)
pinyin: lin2 zi5 da4 le5 , shen2 me5 niao3 dou1 you3

definition: it is nothing/there's nothing ... about it
nothing is impossible/there's nothing impossible about it
pinyin: mei2 you3 shen2 me5 bu4 ke3 neng2

sentences.english: What sequela is there after becoming gall-stone operation?
sentences.chinese: 做了胆结石手术后有什么后遗症吗？

sentences.english: What were the subtexts of this venerable tale?
sentences.chinese: 这部古老的童话所暗含的意义是什么呢？

sentences.english: Do you know what his whereabouts are?
sentences.chinese: 你知道他现在的所在之处是什么？

sentences.english: And why do we fall for it, year after year?
sentences.chinese: 而我们又为什么年复一年为之倾倒？

sentences.english: The amount of time you spend alone has little to do with being lonely.
sentences.chinese: 你大部分独自一人的时间想必和寂寞扯不上什么关系。

sentences.english: Man is the only creature that consumes without producing.
sentences.chinese: 人是一种最可怜的家伙，什么都产不了，只会挥霍。

sentences.english: What did these tattoos look like?
sentences.chinese: 这些纹身看起来像什么？

sentences.english: Why should cattle not graze near yew trees?
sentences.chinese: 为什么牛不在紫杉附近吃草？

sentences.english: She never learned how to read a milometer,or any meter.
sentences.chinese: 不管是里程表，还是什么表，她从来就不会看。

sentences.english: You see, I know how Kirstie feels.
sentences.chinese: 你看，我知道柯斯迪什么感觉。

sentences.english: Where had he obtained that blouse?
sentences.chinese: 那件布罩衫，他是从什么地方得来的呢？

sentences.english: Why should the wind do his bidding? The wind is just wind.
sentences.chinese: 为什么风要为他服务呢？，风就是风。

sentences.english: What Is Unique About the Program?
sentences.chinese: 蒙氏教学方法独特之处是什么？

sentences.english: Which soup do you want? We have Eggdrop Soup with Sliced Tomatoes, Famous Hot &Sour Soup.
sentences.chinese: 您来点什么汤？我们有番茄蛋花汤，酸辣汤。

sentences.english: Scientists don't yet know what the effects of those reactions might be.
sentences.chinese: 科学家们还不清楚这些反应会具体产生什么样的结果。

definition: dialectal equivalent of 什麼|什么[shen2 me5]/also pr. [sha4]
anyway/in any case/to come over from the enemy's side
how much?/how many?/(phone number, student ID etc) what number?
variant of 怎麼|怎么[zen3 me5]
how?/how about?/how was it?/how are things?
classifier indicating a small amount or small number greater than 1: some, a few, several
how old?/how big?/how much?/so big/that much
finally/in the end/when all is said and done/after all/to the end/to the last

particle indicating that a previously asked question is to be applied to the preceding word ("What about ...?", "And ...?")/particle for inquiring about location ("Where is ...?")/particle signaling a pause, to emphasize the preceding words and allow the listener time to take them on board ("ok?", "are you with me?")/(at the end of a declarative sentence) particle indicating continuation of a state or action/particle indicating strong affirmation
youngest/most junior/tiny/one (unambiguous spoken form when spelling out numbers, esp. on telephone or in military)/one or ace on dice or dominoes/variant of 吆[yao1], to shout
(before a noun) Do (you, they etc) have ...?/Is there a ...?/(before a verb) Did (you, they etc) (verb, infinitive)?/Have (you, they etc) (verb, past participle)?
